NOTES ON THE LESSON AND PROJECT 15/2/2023
------------------------------------------
# in the base html file

first link using ginger
put your content for all pages there
add a ginger block tag:
{% block content %}
{% endblock %}

# in the other html files
extend the ginger to the base html file
write a :
{% extends 'base.html' %}
write a :
{% block content %}
Then put the content for that page here
{% endblock %}


*******************************************
its more secure to use the name than the route name
*******************************************
instead of writing the :
/about
you can use ginger and write the name allocated:
"{% url 'my-home' %}"
